Docker System & Info
_____________________________________________________________
| Command            | Purpose                              |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------ |
| `docker version`   | Show Docker client & server versions |
| `docker info`      | Docker daemon & system info          |
| `docker system df` | Disk usage by Docker                 |
| `docker stats`     | Real-time container resource usage   |


Image Management
_______________________________________________
| Command                  | Purpose           |
| ------------------------ | ----------------- |
| `docker images`          | List local images |
| `docker pull <image>`    | Download image    |
| `docker build -t name .` | Build image       |
| `docker rmi <image>`     | Remove image      |
| `docker tag`             | Tag an image      |


Container Lifecycle
_______________________________________________
| Command          | Purpose                  |
| ---------------- | ------------------------ |
| `docker run`     | Create + start container |
| `docker create`  | Create container only    |
| `docker start`   | Start container          |
| `docker stop`    | Graceful stop            |
| `docker kill`    | Force stop               |
| `docker restart` | Restart container        |
| `docker rm`      | Remove container         |


Container Inspection & Logs
______________________________________________
| Command               | Purpose            |
| --------------------- | ------------------ |
| `docker ps`           | Running containers |
| `docker ps -a`        | All containers     |
| `docker logs <id>`    | View logs          |
| `docker inspect <id>` | Detailed metadata  |
| `docker top <id>`     | Running processes  |


Execute Commands Inside Container
__________________________________________________
| Command         | Purpose                      |
| --------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `docker exec`   | Run command inside container |
| `docker attach` | Attach to STDOUT             |


Networking
________________________________________________
| Command                  | Purpose           |
| ------------------------ | ----------------- |
| `docker network ls`      | List networks     |
| `docker network create`  | Create network    |
| `docker network inspect` | Inspect network   |
| `docker network connect` | Connect container |


Volumes & Storage
____________________________________________
| Command                 | Purpose        |
| ----------------------- | -------------- |
| `docker volume ls`      | List volumes   |
| `docker volume create`  | Create volume  |
| `docker volume inspect` | Inspect volume |
| `docker volume rm`      | Remove volume  |

Cleanup & Maintenance
________________________________________________________
| Command                  | Purpose                   |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------- |
| `docker system prune`    | Clean unused resources    |
| `docker container prune` | Remove stopped containers |
| `docker image prune`     | Remove dangling images    |
| `docker volume prune`    | Remove unused volumes     |


Docker Commit & Save
________________________________________
| Command         | Purpose             |
| --------------- | ------------------- |
| `docker commit` | Container â†’ Image   |
| `docker save`   | Save image to tar   |
| `docker load`   | Load image from tar |


Docker Compose
_________________________________________
| Command               | Purpose        |
| --------------------- | -------------- |
| `docker-compose up`   | Start services |
| `docker-compose down` | Stop services  |
| `docker-compose ps`   | List services  |
| `docker-compose logs` | View logs      |
__________________________________________


docker tag my-app:1.0 \ <account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:1.0   -> Tag Image for ECR
docker push <account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:1.0               -> Push Image to ECR
docker pull <account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:1.0               -> Pull Image from ECR
docker run -d \ --name my-app-container \ -p 80:80 \ <account-id>.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:1.0    -> Run Container from ECR Image


